                     <interp inst="t18230910-79-defend898" type="age" value="63"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18230910-79-off449" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18230910-79-off449" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-79-off449" type="offenceSubcategory" value="housebreaking"></interp>
               feloniously breaking and entering the dwelling-house of 
                     
                        <persName id="t18230910-79-victim900" type="victimName">
                           William 
                           Mitchell
                        <interp inst="t18230910-79-victim900" type="surname" value="Mitchell"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18230910-79-victim900" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18230910-79-victim900" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-79-off449 t18230910-79-victim900"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , about the hour of four in the forenoon, of the <rs id="t18230910-79-cd450" type="crimeDate">13th of August</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-79-off449 t18230910-79-cd450"></join>, at Christchurch, (the said 
                     <persName id="t18230910-79-person901">
                        William 
                        Mittchell
                     <interp inst="t18230910-79-person901" type="surname" value="Mittchell"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18230910-79-person901" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18230910-79-person901" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  , and other persons being therein) and stealing therein a cannister, value 2 d., and three ounces of tea, value 15 d.
            </rs>, his property.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230910-79-person902">
                  WILLIAM 
                  MITCHELL
               <interp inst="t18230910-79-person902" type="surname" value="MITCHELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-79-person902" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-79-person902" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in the parish of <placeName id="t18230910-79-crimeloc451">Christ-church, Spitalfields</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-79-crimeloc451" type="placeName" value="Christ-church, Spitalfields"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-79-crimeloc451" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-79-off449 t18230910-79-crimeloc451"></join>, and rent the house. On the night of the 13th of August, I latched my door, but do not think that I locked it. My wife awoke me about a quarter to four o'clock; it was then light - I came down, and found the prisoner taking some things off the line down stairs - he ran out; I pursued him; the watchman took him, and found some tea in a cannister of mine upon him, which he had taken from my safe. My children were in the house.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230910-79-person903">
                  SAMUEL 
                  GREEN
               <interp inst="t18230910-79-person903" type="surname" value="GREEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-79-person903" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-79-person903" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. I apprehended him, and took the cannister from him.</p>
               <p>(Cannister produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner made no Defence.</p>
